                <h1>How to Obtain a Certificate of Good Conduct in Germany</h1>
                <p>In Germany, a certificate of good conduct (Führungszeugnis) is an official document that certifies an individual's criminal record status. It’s commonly required for employment, visa applications, or volunteering. To obtain it, applicants must submit a request to the local police or the Federal Office of Justice, often needing identification and a fee.</p>
